        <h1>PlantVisorPRO Locale: features and benefits</h1>
        <p>PlantVisorPRO is a Web supervision system designed for the HVAC/R market to monitor and supervise sites.</p>
        <p>PlantVisorPRO Locale functions let the user fully manage alarms, site setup, work normally performed by installers, and monitor (local and remote) site status. The simple and efficient interface makes it easy to use.</p>
        <h2>Configuration</h2>
        <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
            <li class="p" value="1">
                <p>PlantVisorPRO Locale can be easily set for system operations. A <span style="font-weight: bold;">Device template library</span> (standard or custom) is provided to quickly acquire field device setups, immediately manage alarms and record data. When PlantVisorPRO Locale is set, it can immediately monitor system status.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="p" value="2">
                <p>Special device and user profile  <span style="font-weight: bold;">setup propagation</span> functions avoid typically repetitive setup procedures. Alarm monitoring, reports, graphs and all notification activities are based on <span style="font-weight: bold;">alarm and log variable management</span> policies. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Auxiliary relay</span> management policies (timed and non) combine field interventions.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="p" value="3">
                <p>The chance to create <span style="font-weight: bold;">logical groups</span> makes accessing, managing and maintaining devices typical of refrigeration systems (i.e.: normal temperature counters, low temperature counters, frozen food islands and dairy counters) easier. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Group</span> divisions let personal control physically or logically similar devices, setting the same parameters on the different devices by pressing only one button. Similar to physical devices,<span style="font-weight: bold;"> logical</span> devices let you monitor variables on different physical devices and logical variables, the result of calculations and algorithms.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="p" value="4">
                <p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Custom function </span>versatility fully adapts final results to user needs. Different privileges or device groups can be assigned using <span style="font-weight: bold;">user profiles</span>. This way, special privileges can be assigned to specialized personnel (i.e. conditioning system technician) without risking accidental changes to the original setup. <span style="font-weight: bold;">Graph and curve aspects</span> can be edited based on data visibility levels (global, device group or single device) and can be assigned to specific user profiles. The logon page <span style="font-weight: bold;">logo and background image </span>can be customized. Similarly, <span style="font-weight: bold;">reports</span>, previously set by the installer and launched at set intervals without any user intervention, can also be customized. The <span style="font-weight: bold;">main device monitoring page</span> can be organized according to which variables are most significant and need greater visibility. </p>
            </li>
            <li class="p" value="5">
                <p>If custom function versatility is combined with <span style="font-weight: bold;">Layout Editor</span> and <span style="font-weight: bold;">PlantVisorPRO SDK</span> programming, custom synoptic maps and custom pages can also be created.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Monitoring and supervision</h2>
        <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
            <li class="p" value="1">
                <p>Sites can be monitored on several levels (global, group or single device levels) and in different modes (with synoptic maps, with device summaries, with a full device list) and each "view" can be enabled for users with different needs.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="p" value="2">
                <p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Alarm</span> signals are easy to consult and let Service technicians acknowledge alarms, stop associated actions or force alarms clear.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="p" value="3">
                <p>Other <span style="font-weight: bold;">signals to remote devices</span> (i.e.: text messages, faxes, e-mail) or field actions guarantee immediate and autonomous system intervention in the event of fault situations and guarantee prompt notifications to maintenance personnel.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="p" value="4">
                <p>Field behavior analysis is made easier by graphs and reports (HACCP and logs). <span style="font-weight: bold;">Graphs</span> are dynamically created according to user needs and can include heterogeneous data (i.e.: temperatures and relay status), scales (each parameter can be displayed with its own scale) and colors. In addition to default <span style="font-weight: bold;">reports</span> printed at regular intervals, reports can be created on demand and detailed reports printed for the required band.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Safety and stability</h2>
        <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
            <li class="p" value="1">
                <p>PlantVisorPRO Locale and PlantVisorPRO Embedded operations are controlled by an external component: <span style="font-weight: bold;">guardianPRO</span>. it extends typical field supervision notifications adding notifications tied to potential software and hardware faults, failed alarm management and sudden "frozen" field variable values.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="p" value="2">
                <p>To permit reconstruction setup and system changes, personal <span style="font-weight: bold;">notes</span> can be added and regularly sent to RemotePRO. Each <span style="font-weight: bold;">note</span> belongs to its author who is the only one with editing rights. </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
